Summary:
This deck combines a high-pass and low-pass RC section to make a passive band-pass response. It passes an intermediate frequency region and reduces both ends of the spectrum.
The topology is simple but useful for illustrating how cascaded first-order sections shape frequency response.

Line-by-line:
`V1 N001 0 SINE(1 1 25000) AC 1` is the drive source.
`C2 N002 N001 100µ` and `R2 N002 0 1` form the input high-pass branch.
`R1 OUT N002 1` and `C1 OUT 0 100µ` form the output low-pass branch.
`.ac dec 1000 10 100k` sweeps the response.
The comments label it as an RC band-pass filter.

Netlist meaning:
The intermediate node `N002` is the point where the high-pass stage hands off to the low-pass stage.
The output is taken after the low-pass section at `OUT`.
